    <div class="article-teaser">
        Refurbishment work to improve lift services at Shadwell station as part of Transport for London's (TfL) 5-Year &pound;10bn investment programme are to begin on Monday 3 October 2005.
        
    </div>



 <div class="on-this-page">
<div class="pullquote right">
                        <p>
                            Every weekday, 4,700 people use Shadwell station
                            
                        </p>
                    </div>
                
            
            
            <p>Both lifts will be extensively refurbished one at a time to improve reliability, taking approximately 10 weeks each to complete. </p>
<p>The second lift will only be taken out of service when the first lift is back in operation. </p>
<p>Customers are advised that they may have to wait slightly longer to use the lift while these works are carried out. </p>
<p>The refurbishment works are expected to be completed by March 2006.<br></p>
            <ul>
<li>Transport for London (TfL) is investing &pound;10bn over the next five years to improve and expand London's transport network, more than half of that in the Tube</li>
<li>Metronet Rail SSL are responsible for the maintenance and renewal of the Circle, District, Hammersmith &amp; City, Metropolitan and East London lines</li>
<li>Opened in 1876, 4,700 people use Shadwell station every weekday</li>
<li>The East London Line will close in 2008 so that the line can be extended and is scheduled to re-open in 2010</li></ul>

     

        
        
        
